title: Google\Cloud\AIPlatform\V1\Endpoint
name: Endpoint
description:
Models are deployed into it, and afterwards Endpoint is called to obtain predictions and explanations.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The resource name of the Endpoint.

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Required. The display name of the Endpoint. The name can be up to 128 characters long and can be consist of any UTF-8 characters.

params.name: data.description
params.description: The description of the Endpoint.

params.name: data.deployed_models
params.description: Output only. The models deployed in this Endpoint. To add or remove DeployedModels use [EndpointService.DeployModel][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.EndpointService.DeployModel] and [EndpointService.UndeployModel][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.EndpointService.UndeployModel] respectively.

params.name: data.traffic_split
params.description: A map from a DeployedModel's ID to the percentage of this Endpoint's traffic that should be forwarded to that DeployedModel. If a DeployedModel's ID is not listed in this map, then it receives no traffic. The traffic percentage values must add up to 100, or map must be empty if the Endpoint is to not accept any traffic at a moment.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Used to perform consistent read-modify-write updates. If not set, a blind "overwrite" update happens.

params.name: data.labels
params.description: The labels with user-defined metadata to organize your Endpoints. Label keys and values can be no longer than 64 characters (Unicode codepoints), can only contain lowercase letters, numeric characters, underscores and dashes. International characters are allowed. See https://goo.gl/xmQnxf for more information and examples of labels.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. Timestamp when this Endpoint was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. Timestamp when this Endpoint was last updated.

params.name: data.encryption_spec
params.description: Customer-managed encryption key spec for an Endpoint. If set, this Endpoint and all sub-resources of this Endpoint will be secured by this key.

params.name: data.network
params.description: The full name of the Google Compute Engine network to which the Endpoint should be peered. Private services access must already be configured for the network. If left unspecified, the Endpoint is not peered with any network. Only one of the fields, [network][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint.network] or [enable_private_service_connect][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint.enable_private_service_connect], can be set. Format: projects/{project}/global/networks/{network}. Where {project} is a project number, as in 12345, and {network} is network name.

params.name: data.enable_private_service_connect
params.description: Deprecated: If true, expose the Endpoint via private service connect. Only one of the fields, [network][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint.network] or [enable_private_service_connect][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.Endpoint.enable_private_service_connect], can be set.

params.name: data.model_deployment_monitoring_job
params.description: Output only. Resource name of the Model Monitoring job associated with this Endpoint if monitoring is enabled by [CreateModelDeploymentMonitoringJob][]. Format: projects/{project}/locations/{location}/modelDeploymentMonitoringJobs/{model_deployment_monitoring_job}

params.name: data.predict_request_response_logging_config
params.description: Configures the request-response logging for online prediction.
